what can i put in my cubboards to repel mice they are chewing my best towels it s not what you can put in it s what you have to take out mice only live where there is a source of food so even if your house is clean they will still stay in your home first thing i can suggest you do is keep all food stuff in tight lidded container s sweep the kitchen floor or better still pass the hoover when ever you finish working in the kitchen at night and the garbage is put outside before going to bed they work at night looking for the smallest morsel to eat any cracks or small holes fill then with cement and cover with fine wire set trap s with bate of either chocolate or peanut butter best not to use poison because if you can t reach the dead mouse you will then have another problem with the smell you can put mothballs and peppermint in the cupboards where you keep your towel s but this will give you yet another problem how to rid the smell from the towels try find the holes they are coming from and seal them don t invite them to stay for dinner Hamster Kitchen Fancy rat The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Peanut butter Customs and etiquette of Japan Poker jargon Vermicompost Fecal incontinence Drag racing RuneScape quests Food Phoebe Buffay's songs Brewery Sento Cuisine of Denmark Bedbug Spidey Super Stories World War Three (Doctor Who) Textile manufacturing Japanese cuisine Breakfast Coconut crab Ferret Episodes of Lost (Season 1) AFI 100 Years series American Black Bear Tofu Mouse (computing) Plastic Guinea pig Babe Ruth The Curse of Fenric Japanese tea ceremony Naval mine Dairy Diseases of the honeybee Social rule Upholstery Bread Brush Discworld gods Vacuum tube Electrophysiology Guess Who's Coming to Criticize Dinner? Bulk vending Garfield Chocolate Japanese toilet Peanut Menstrual cup Salad Fingers Mattress Sushi Knife Cannabis cultivation Shaggy dog story Charlie and the Chocolate Factory (film) The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy Primary and Secondary Phases Sweet Sm